reviewText: Beautiful! I enjoyed the imagery and excellent photography.  The music was not the greatest.  I hosted a luau at the house and had this playing on a big TV for background and mood.  I muted the show so it was perfect for our situation.  Glad we had prime!  Better to rent for a couple of bucks than buy a $22 DVD that I wouldn't use again.

Terrible movie. All it is is a movie with average video. No words just music and it repeats itself in certain spots. I learned nothing new or even knew what island the movie was filmed on. Do not buy this. Boring. Snooze faces.
Beautiful and with fine music too

The scenery is lovely and the music is fine, but I would prefer no music--just the sounds of nature.  I would also be happy with fewer places.  I like it playing in the background so I can look up once in a while and feel like I am really there.
Soothing music and wonderful ocean and breeze sounds if you had a fan on you would think you were there. Loved it went right to sleep.
this puts my son and I to sleep we love watching the beautiful landscapes and the calming music
Pretty bit music is not Hawaiian and some scenery is not very Hawaiian looking either. I have been there and there is just so much to choose from and this was very plain.
Without any narration we're not sure what we are seeing or where in Hawaii we are. Film Q OK.
